dashboard and that relevant candidates are simply flowing into our [Applica=
nt Tracking System], saving me so much time on sourcing. Because of Joonko,=
 I was able to get back to what really matters =E2=80=93 hiring great talen=
t.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Those are al=
l from <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35681542.25=
7302/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9maWxlcy9saXRpZ2F0aW9uL2NvbXBsYWludHMvMjAyNC=
9jb21wLXByMjAyNC03MC5wZGY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cC6a353d65" itemprop=3D"St=
oryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000;=
 text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-=
color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">the co=
mplaint</a> in a US Securities and Exchange Commission <a href=3D"https://l=
ink.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35681542.257302/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLm=
dvdi9uZXdzL3ByZXNzLXJlbGVhc2UvMjAyNC03MA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB5eabc44a"=
 itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"=
color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px;=
 border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color=
: #ccc;">lawsuit</a> against Ilit Raz, the founder of a startup called Joon=
ko, which purportedly used artificial intelligence to help companies hire d=
iverse job candidates. Federal prosecutors also <a href=3D"https://link.mai=
l.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35681542.257302/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuanVzdGljZS5nb=
3YvdXNhby1zZG55L3ByL2ZvdW5kZXItYW5kLWZvcm1lci1jZW8tYXJ0aWZpY2lhbC1pbnRlbGxp=
Z2VuY2UtY29tcGFueS1jaGFyZ2VkLXNlY3VyaXRpZXMtZnJhdWQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23=
cB0f661272" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank=
" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-=
width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backg=
round-color: #ccc;">brought a criminal case</a>. There is plenty of egregio=
us stuff here; from the criminal case:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 1=
6px 0;">In or about 2023, a Joonko investor (=E2=80=9CInvestor-1=E2=80=9D) =
became suspicious about Joonko=E2=80=99s performance and requested certain =
information from Joonko, including bank statements. =C2=A0In response, on o=
r about April 3, 2023, RAZ emailed Investor-1 a purported Joonko bank state=
ment, which depicted that the company had an average balance of over $5,000=
,000. =C2=A0In truth and in fact, and as RAZ well knew, the bank records th=
at RAZ emailed to Investor-1 were forged, and the actual bank records showe=
d that Joonko=E2=80=99s true account balance was millions of dollars lower.=
 =C2=A0Less than a week later, on or about April 8, 2023, RAZ emailed Inves=
tor-1 a set of purported purchase orders for Joonko customers. =C2=A0RAZ kn=
ew that many of the purchase orders she emailed to Investor-1 were fictitio=
us, contained forged signatures, and were executed on behalf of purported c=
ustomers that had no business relationship with Joonko.</p></blockquote><p =
style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">You can=E2=80=99t forge bank statements or signat=
ures on purchase orders! That=E2=80=99s bad. On the other hand, is Raz the =
first startup CEO to write fake customer=C2=A0<em>testimonials</em>? Is she=
 the first startup CEO to be a bit aspirational=C2=A0<em>on her LinkedIn pr=
ofile</em>?=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">My sense has always been =
that, if you are a public company, <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbu=
siness.com/click/35681542.257302/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW=
9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDItMDMvZ29sZG1hbi1zYWNocy1nb2VzLXRvLXN1cHJlbWUtY291c=
nQtaGVkZ2UtZnVuZHMtd29uLW9uLWdhbWVzdG9wLWtrcG9lNndzP2NtcGlkPUJCRDA2MTEyNF9N=
T05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJ=
tPTI0MDYxMSZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB5c4115=
07" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-c=
olor: #ccc;">everything is securities fraud</a>: You have to be scrupulousl=
y truthful in all of your public communications, and if investors can find =
the slightest arguable misstatement they will sue you for securities fraud.=
 And if you are actually <em>lying about your customers and revenue</em>, y=
ou will go to prison.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">At private startups, =
on the other hand, the rules have usually been a bit laxer. Not as a legal =
matter, but as a practical matter. Fewer people see your statements, for on=
e thing. (They=E2=80=99re not public.) Those people are more likely to be s=
ympathetic venture capitalists, who probably won=E2=80=99t sue you or turn =
you in to the authorities if you=E2=80=99re lying. Also, your stock does no=
t trade continuously, so nobody can say =E2=80=9CI was deceived by that int=
erview you did and bought your stock.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0The stock only trades w=
hen you sell it in defined fundraising rounds, so you can take some liberti=
es on your LinkedIn as long as you walk them back in the official investor =
presentations. (Not legal advice!)</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But my s=
ense is also that <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/=
35681542.257302/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS92aWV3L2FydGljbGVzLzIwMTg=
tMDQtMDQvc29tZXRoaW5nLWlzLWxvc3Qtd2hlbi1jb21wYW5pZXMtc3RheS1wcml2YXRlP2NtcG=
lkPUJCRDA2MTEyNF9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzb=
GV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTI0MDYxMSZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8=
524a319a23cB33dc9b90" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: so=
lid; background-color: #ccc;">private markets are the new public markets</a=
>: As startups raise millions of dollars from institutions and individuals,=
 and stay private longer, it does make more sense that the rules of public =
markets increasingly apply to private ones. These days, if you puff up your=
 LinkedIn as a startup CEO, that can get you in just as much trouble as it =
would if you were a public-company CEO.</p><table class=3D"header" width=3D=
